## Render-site action bar pattern (no per-message subscriptions)

When a list container needs action buttons (retry, delete, copy) on its child entities, render those buttons **in the list item builder of the parent**, not inside the child entity's `render` method.

- Child emits events + parent subscribes per child → N subscriptions, `Vec<gpui::Subscription>` lifetime management, stale callbacks on truncation/delete.
- Parent reads child state at render time and calls child methods directly via entity update → zero subscriptions, always consistent with current list state.

Applied to `ChatPanel`: the action bar (⟳ retry, × delete, ⎘ copy) is built in the list item closure in `chat_panel.rs`, not inside `ChatMessageView::render`. The closure captures a `WeakEntity<ChatPanel>` and calls `retry_message`, `delete_message_at`, etc. via `handle.update(cx, ...)`.

**Rule:** Future per-message actions should follow this render-site pattern. Do NOT reintroduce a `msg_subscriptions: Vec<gpui::Subscription>` vector.

