## Stale-capture bug in click handlers

If a click handler captures a **computed value** at render time from a nested entity (e.g. `msg.read(cx).copy_text_for_context(cx)`), and that value depends on state inside the nested entity that does NOT notify the parent — the captured value will be stale by click time.

**Symptom:** Right-click copy returns old text even though the selection changed.

**Fix:** Capture the `Entity<T>` itself (clone it into the closure), then call the accessor **at click time** inside the handler:

```rust
let msg = msg.clone();
on_click(move |_, window, cx| {
    let text = msg.read(cx).copy_text_for_context(cx);
    window.write_to_clipboard(ClipboardItem::new_string(text));
})
```

This applies to any closure that reads from a child entity whose notifications do not propagate to the parent. In the chat panel, `TextFieldView` selection changes notify only `TextFieldView` — not `ChatPanel` — so any render-time capture of selection-dependent state from `ChatMessageView` will be stale.

---

## Context menu — deferred+anchored overlay with comprehensive dismissal

GPUI 0.2.2 has no built-in context menu widget. Pattern used in `TextFieldView` and `ChatPanel`:

1. Store `context_menu_pos: Option<Point<Pixels>>` in view state.
2. On right-click (`on_mouse_down(MouseButton::Right, ...)`): set `context_menu_pos = Some(event.position)`, `cx.stop_propagation()`, `cx.notify()`.
3. Render via `deferred(anchored().position(pos).child(menu_div))` inside the element tree. `deferred()` paints after all siblings so the menu floats above them.
4. **Dismiss triggers — all four are required:**
   - `on_mouse_down_out` (capture phase) — clears `context_menu_pos` before the click is processed elsewhere. Prevents stale menus when right-clicking a different field.
   - Left-click inside the field — clears menu before handling the click.
   - Focus loss (`on_focus_change` / focus-transition block in `render`) — clears menu.
   - `Escape` key in `on_key_down` — clears menu, checked before Ctrl shortcuts.
5. Menu item clicks must call `cx.stop_propagation()` after handling to prevent the click from re-triggering dismiss handlers.

**Empty menu shortcut:** if there would be no visible items (e.g. read-only field with no selection → no Copy, no Paste), return early from the right-click handler WITHOUT calling `cx.stop_propagation()`. This lets outer containers (e.g. the chat row) receive the event and open their own menu.
